    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my tomato plants are acting weird. the leaves on the bottom are turning all yellow and kind of pale. any idea what happened or how to fix it?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yellowing lower leaves on tomato plants, especially when they look pale, is a classic sign of a few things, like a nutrient deficiency or watering issues. It's often related to nitrogen deficiency, which is a common problem, or sometimes overwatering can cause similar symptoms. You can try applying a balanced, slow-release fertilizer to give them a boost, and make sure you're watering deeply but not constantly soggy. If the problem persists, check the soil moisture levels carefully.",
